      "levels": [
        {"front": "hand", "back": "la mano", "grammarNote": "With reflexive verbs and body parts, Spanish uses the definite article (la, el, los, las) instead of a possessive. 'Lávate las manos' = Wash your hands (not 'lava tus manos'). 'Me rompí el brazo' = I broke my arm. The reflexive pronoun (me/te/se) makes clear whose body part it is."},
